[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bristol City Women 0-3 Manchester City Women

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Toni Duggan scored an 18-minute hat-trick as Manchester City won at Bristol City in the Women's Super League One Spring Series.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The England forward turned in Nikita Parris' cross at the back post and then scored her second from the spot after Jennifer Beattie was fouled.
Duggan completed her hat-trick after combining well with Parris, who had earlier hit the post.
Chloe Arthur went close for the hosts but was denied by Marie Hourihan.
Bristol City forward Claire Emslie also had a chance when she was gifted the ball but fired over.
Duggan was a threat all evening and went close three times in a nine-minute spell in the first half as she hit the crossbar, put a header wide, and fired over from 25 yards.
Manchester City have now won two of their first three matches this season to sit second in the table, while Bristol City have three points from their opening four games.
